The most aggressive candidate will win the Wiper ticket for the Mombasa governor race, Nyali MP Hezron Awiti has said.On Sunday he said only Mombasa residents will decide who will become Wiper&rsquo;s flagbearer, seeking to allay fears that there might be a party favourite.Mombasa Senator Hassan Omar has often said t primaries will be free and fair and all candidates will have an equal opportunity. He was not available for comment on Tuesday.Awiti and Omar, both Wiper national officials, have declared interest in the governor&rsquo;s seat. This has created a difficult scenario for Cord. Governor Hassan Joho is from ODM, a Cord party.Awiti and Omar have rejected calls for joint Cord nominations.